  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A document may contain the responsibilities and expectations for developers during the code review process, such as&#xD;
    preparing the code for review, responding to feedback, and making necessary changes.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Guidance:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    1. Ensure that the code is following the coding standards defined by the organization or team.&lt;br />&#xD;
    2. Make sure that the code is written in an efficient and maintainable manner.&lt;br />&#xD;
    3. Ensure that the code is properly documented with clear and concise comments.&lt;br />&#xD;
    4. Include error handling and exception handling in the code to handle unexpected scenarios.&lt;br />&#xD;
    5. Avoid hardcoding of values and use constants or variables instead.&lt;br />&#xD;
    6. Ensure that the code is modular and follows the principle of separation of concerns.&lt;br />&#xD;
    7. Avoid unnecessary complexity in the code by breaking it down into smaller and simpler functions.&lt;br />&#xD;
    8. Ensure that the code is properly tested and all test cases are passed.&lt;br />&#xD;
    9. Be open to feedback and suggestions from the reviewers and make necessary changes to the code accordingly.&lt;br />&#xD;
    10. Ensure that the code is properly reviewed before committing it to the codebase.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
